# Website Utils-Composed Brand Marks

Applies when authoring or replacing **custom dual-tone / brand marks** shared across shells (not Feather `IconType` glyphs).

## Rule

1. Shared marks live under `website/src/app/ui/components/` (not under `customer/`) so landing and customer can both import them.
2. Compose with `Box` / `Row` / `Col` + `semanticColor` tokens, export `React.FC` + `withMemo`.
3. Do **not** implement these marks as `forwardRef` + `IconBaseProps` SVG that calls `useThemeManager` / hardcodes `me-icon` / invents a parallel icon system.
4. RTL mirroring for start-side asymmetry: prefer flex start-side layout (first child = start) so `dir=rtl` flips naturally. Use `Icn` `flp` only for true directional Feather glyphs.
5. Customer `HeaderIconButton` accepts marks via the `icon` ReactNode branch; landing header embeds the same mark directly.
6. Shared home mark: `HomeMark` via `rootMark` / `Crumb.mark` / drawer tile `mark` (ReactNode) — not Feather `FiHome` when dual-tone brand chrome is intended. Use `tone="onPrimary"` on navy action wells.

## Canonical cases

- `DrawerMenuIcon` (`website/src/app/ui/components/DrawerMenuIcon.tsx`): accent rail + two ink bars, default `size={1.2}`. Used by `CustomerHeader` and `LandingHeader` (replacing `FiMenu` on landing).
- `HomeMark` (`website/src/app/ui/components/HomeMark.tsx`): portal frame + accent floor rail; `tone="ink"` (breadcrumb) / `tone="onPrimary"` (drawer home tile).

## Why

Forcing brand marks through `react-icons` `IconType` fought dual colors and RTL. Keeping the mark under `customer/` blocked landing reuse.
